# Accessibility Engine — Project Roadmap

This roadmap outlines possible stages of exploration and development for the Accessibility Engine concept.

Accessibility Engine is currently in the concept and architecture stage. The roadmap describes potential directions for research and prototyping rather than fixed product milestones.

---

## Phase 1 — Concept and Architecture (Current Stage)

The current phase focuses on defining and documenting the core concept.

Activities include:

- defining system architecture
- documenting framework layers
- outlining ethical and safety considerations
- exploring agentic AI mediation models
- developing accessible project documentation

The goal of this phase is to clarify how accessibility mediation systems may function.

---

## Phase 2 — Prototype Exploration

Future work may involve small prototype experiments to test key concepts.

Possible prototype areas include:

- detecting accessibility barriers in web interfaces
- assisting users with inaccessible forms
- generating accessible workflow guidance
- interpreting interface structure using AI

These prototypes would serve as proof-of-concept experiments.

---

## Phase 3 — Accessibility Mediation Experiments

This phase may explore how adaptive systems assist users in completing complex workflows.

Research areas include:

- human-AI collaboration models
- adaptive guidance systems
- balancing autonomy and user control
- user interaction with mediated workflows

---

## Phase 4 — Assistive Technology Integration

Future work may investigate integration with existing assistive technologies.

Areas of exploration include:

- screen reader interoperability
- voice interaction systems
- magnification tools
- alternative input methods

The goal is to augment existing assistive technologies rather than replace them.

---

## Phase 5 — Real-World Evaluation

Long-term exploration may evaluate accessibility mediation systems in real-world contexts.

Examples include:

- healthcare intake systems
- service portals
- digital kiosks
- institutional workflows

These evaluations would examine whether mediation systems meaningfully reduce accessibility barriers.

---

## Long-Term Vision

Accessibility Engine explores the possibility of human-adaptive accessibility systems that support equitable participation across digital and physical environments.

The long-term goal is to develop systems that:

- adapt to user needs
- preserve user autonomy
- operate safely and transparently
- integrate with existing technologies
